My favorite stories on /x/ are always the ones about creepy small towns in the middle of nothing. An isolated environment that can foster true terror. There are a lot of these even in Europe. I've mentioned the one here that disappeared a few gypsies who wandered nearby forever.

Like there was that one town where everyone had missing arms and legs and apparently the insurance they had wasnt even that good and there were rumors of some cult. There was that one old town everyone just left one day after for a few weeks there were lights in the sky at night

There was an old greentext on /x/ about an anon's grandpa who built a house by himself, but felt weird inside it, especially one room. One night his wife saw him staring at a specific corner there that was "wrong", like it looked geometrically impossible if seen from an angle

He basically realized there was something very wrong in the construction and almost went insane staring at it, ended up filling it up/changing that part of the wall, but still always felt uneasy around where it stood.
